cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.DL, cs.PL

The paper discusses open science in the context of software engineering, which is the primary focus of the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper also touches upon topics related to cybersecurity (cs.CY), such as sharing data and code securely, and to cryptography (cs.CR), such as discussing the limitations of double-blind reviewing. Additionally, the paper discusses issues related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and programming languages (cs.PL), such as choosing appropriate licenses for open source software and sharing preprints.
